FeedPackage.Description:
Client library to communication with Signere.no REST API. The library contains relevant model classes and a client class with methods to access all resources provided in the Signere.no API. The client class itself is implemented from an interface to make it easily testable.
All explicit communication with the API is handled internally and translated to POCO objects. The client methods require certain fields from Signere.no user credentials in order to work properly. To create a user account and obtain these credentials, please visit signere.no .
Also, check out the REST API documentation at Https://api.signere.no for further details about the resources that can be accessed through this library.
FeedPackage.Tags: Signere Sign BankID Digital signatur Uni Pluss Signere.no
FeedPackage.Title: Unipluss.Sign.ClientNET35

Client library to communication with Signere.no REST API. The library contains relevant model classes and a client class with methods to access all resources provided in the Signere.no API. The client class itself is implemented from an interface to make it easily testable.
All explicit communication with the API is handled internally and translated to POCO objects. The client methods require certain fields from Signere.no user credentials in order to work properly. To create a user account and obtain these credentials, please visit signere.no .
Also, check out the REST API documentation at Https://api.signere.no for further details about the resources that can be accessed through this library.

All explicit communication with the API is handled internally and translated to POCO objects. The client methods require certain fields from Signere.no user credentials in order to work properly. To create a user account and obtain these credentials, please visit signere.no .
Also, check out the REST API documentation at Https://api.signere.no for further details about the resources that can be accessed through this library.
FeedPackage.Tags: Signere Sign BankID Digital signatur Uni Pluss Signere.no

FeedPackage.Description: Unidecode.NET is .NET library dll, written in C#. It provides string or char extension method Unidecode() that returns transliterated string. It supports huge amount of languages. And it's very easy to add your language if it's not supported already!
FeedPackage.Summary: It often happens that you have text data in Unicode, but you need to represent it in ASCII. For example when integrating with legacy code that doesn’t support Unicode, or for ease of entry of non-Roman names on a US keyboard, or when constructing ASCII machine identifiers from human-readable Unicode strings that should still be somewhat intelligible (a popular example of this is when making an URL slug from an article title).
FeedPackage.Tags: text, unicode, seo
FeedPackage.Title: Unidecode.NET

FeedPackage.Description:
Client library to communication with Signere.no REST API. The library contains relevant model classes and a client class with methods to access all resources provided in the Signere.no API. The client class itself is implemented from an interface to make it easily testable.
All explicit communication with the API is handled internally and translated to POCO objects. The client methods require certain fields from Signere.no user credentials in order to work properly. To create a user account and obtain these credentials, please visit signere.no .
Also, check out the REST API documentation at Https://api.signere.no for further details about the resources that can be accessed through this library.

Client library to communication with Signere.no REST API. The library contains relevant model classes and a client class with methods to access all resources provided in the Signere.no API. The client class itself is implemented from an interface to make it easily testable.
All explicit communication with the API is handled internally and translated to POCO objects. The client methods require certain fields from Signere.no user credentials in order to work properly. To create a user account and obtain these credentials, please visit signere.no .
Also, check out the REST API documentation at Https://api.signere.no for further details about the resources that can be accessed through this library.

All explicit communication with the API is handled internally and translated to POCO objects. The client methods require certain fields from Signere.no user credentials in order to work properly. To create a user account and obtain these credentials, please visit signere.no .
Also, check out the REST API documentation at Https://api.signere.no for further details about the resources that can be accessed through this library.

FeedPackage.Description: The $1 Unistroke Recognizer is a 2-D single-stroke recognizer designed for rapid prototyping of gesture-based user interfaces. In machine learning terms, $1 is an instance-based nearest-neighbor classifier with a Euclidean scoring function, i.e., a geometric template matcher. $1 is an extension of the proportional shape matching approach used in SHARK2, which itself is an adaptation of Tappert's elastic matching approach with zero look-ahead.
FeedPackage.Summary: A UWP-compatible implementation of the $1 unistroke recognizer
FeedPackage.Title: UnistrokeRecognizer.UWP
